<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 4: CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - VALVE
        LEVER INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>VALVE LEVER INSTALLATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
            <title>INTALL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install valve lever (rocker arm) assembly onto the cylinder head using six (6) cylinder
                    head mounting bolts as follows:
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Insert the rocker arm and shaft assembly with the long cylinder head bolts into
                        their respective bolt holes. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600478">4.78</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Run the long cylinder head bolts in fingertight (except the two end bolts). Place a
                        0.013 mm (0.005 in.) feeler gauge between the outside brackets and the rocker levers to prevent
                        binding. Finger-tighten the remaining two end bolts (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600479">4.79</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the cylinder head bolts in three stages as specified under special torque
                    values.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Check the two end rocker arms for freedom of movement after tightening the cylinder head
                            bolts.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two (2) 0.013mm (0.005 in.) feeler gauges.</para>
                <figure id="ef1600477" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5159" filename="../figeg5/EG5159.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.77 Installing Push Rods</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600478" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5158" filename="../figeg5/EG5158.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.78 Installing Valve Lever Assembly</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600479" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5155" filename="../figeg5/EG5155.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.79 Installing Valve Lever Assembly Mounting Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Adjust valve lash as follows:</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>All valves are adjusted by rotating the engine only twice.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Rotate the crankshaft until the #1 piston is on the compression stroke and the
                        timing arrow on the front cover is in line with the TDC mark on the vibration damper.
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Confirm that the #1 piston is on the compression stroke by turning both push rods by
                                hand to verify that both valves are closed. The valves are closed when the push rods are
                                loose and can be turned easily.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Set valve lash by loosening the lock nut and turning the valve adjustment screw with
                        the appropriate size feeler gauge inserted between the rocker arm and valve stem tip. Tighten
                        the valve adjustment screw until the valve lever can support the feeler gauge. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600480">4.80</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        and "
                        <emph type="bold">SPECIFICATIONS</emph>" for valve lash.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the lock nut once the valve adjustment is set. Remove the feeler gauge.
                        Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600481">4.81</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1600480" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5153" filename="../figeg5/EG5153.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                 scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                        <caption>Figure 4.80 Setting Valve Lash</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1600481" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5152" filename="../figeg5/EG5152.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                 scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                        <caption>Figure 4.81 Tightening Valve Lever Lock Nut</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
